thread.title: Nine in hospital and Great Western Highway closed after four-car crash at Blaxland
thread.title_full: Nine in hospital and Great Western Highway closed after four-car crash at Blaxland

author: Lucy Cormack
title: Nine in hospital and Great Western Highway closed after four-car crash at Blaxland
text:
twitter TWEET More 
Seven adults and two children have been taken to hospital after a four-car crash at Blaxland, in the Blue Mountains, on Sunday morning. 
Emergency services arrived at the scene on the Great Western Highway about 10.40am on Sunday. TRAFFIC: Local diversions underway on the Great Western Highway after an earlier collision at Blaxland. #9News pic.twitter.com/E1YkQ32kKk — Nine News Sydney (@9NewsSyd) February 5, 2017 FYI Only - The Great Western Highway is Closed at Blaxland in both directions due to a serious accident. Please... https://t.co/WSvrqsK6lo — Winmalee RFS (@WinmaleeRFS) February 5, 2017 
NSW Ambulance paramedics treated a total of 11 of people, nine of whom required further treatment. 
Three adults were taken to Westmead Hospital in a serious condition, and four adults were taken to Nepean Hospital with minor injuries, including two women aged 32 and 33, and two males, both 37. Two children were also taken to Westmead Children's Hospital. Advertisement 
Those who were taken to hospital had suffered a variety of chest, neck, leg and hand injuries. 
The Great Western Highway has remained closed in both directions. 
A Transport Management Centre spokeswoman said a crash investigation team arrived on site about 12.40pm and they are trying to open a lane in each direction. 
"There is no way of knowing how long it will take," the spokeswoman said, adding that there was "no detour for heavy vehicles". 
Traffic management services are advising motorists to allow for extra time, as lengthy delays continue. 
Blue Mountains Local Area Command officers have launched an investigation. 
More to come
